SUMMARY:Kicking It at Hermann Park
DESCRIPTION:This summer\, Hermann Park Conservancy will welcome the world to Houston with Kicking It at Hermann Park\, presented by ExxonMobil—a free\, public celebration of culture\, community\, and the unifying spirit of sport. Featuring a dynamic mix of programming\, diverse food offerings\, live entertainment\, and family-friendly activities\, everything will take place in the Commons\, the vibrant 26-acre play and gathering space in the southwest corner of the Park. \n\n📍 The Commons at Hermann Park\n📅 Weekend and select weekdays from June 12 – July 5\n🎟️ Free & open to the public\n\nKicking It at Hermann Park will run on weekends and select weekdays from Friday\, June 12\, through Sunday\, July 5\, offering 15 days of engaging experiences for Houstonians and visitors alike during a globally significant moment for the city. \nThe roster of dynamic programming will include: \n\n🎶 Live music & entertainment\n🍴 Local food trucks & culinary offerings\n🎬 Outdoor movie nights\n⚽ Soccer-inspired play & interactive experiences\n🌿 Nature-based activities\n👨‍👩‍👧 Family-friendly programming\n🎭 Cultural celebrations highlighting Houston’s diversity\n\nThank you to ExxonMobil for their generous support! \n \n+++ \nDATES & THEMES\nStay tuned for more details and a complete programming calendar. Activities are subject to change and more may be added. Visit the Conservancy tent on-site in the Commons for any questions!\n \nWEEKEND ONE (JUNE 12 – JUNE 14) PDF SCHEDULE HERE. \nFriday\, June 12 (5 – 9 p.m.): Kickoff in the Park \n\n5 – 6 PM: Trees for Texas: A Backyard Tree Walk (Astros Foundation Pavilion – The Commons)\n5 – 7 PM: Carousel Karaoke (Lott Family Carousel – The Commons)\n6 – 7 PM: Seeds for Success: The Art of Starting a Garden (Cullen Pavilion – The Commons)\n7 – 8 PM: Perennials in the Park: Garden Discovery Tour (Astros Foundation Pavilion – The Commons)\n7 – 9 PM: Open Decks: Live DJ Experience (Powell Foundation Terrace – between Water Play Area and Space Adventure in the Commons)\n\nSaturday\, June 13 (3 – 10 p.m.): Texas Heritage \n\n3 PM: “One Wan”: Japanese Garden Tea Ceremony (Japanese Garden)\n3 – 4 PM: T is for Texas! Twanda’s Theatre on Wheels from Young Audiences of Houston (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n3 – 4 PM: Hidden Invaders: Understanding Invasive Species (Next to Lott Family Carousel – The Commons)\n4 – 5 PM: Rhythms of Tradition: Mixteco Ballet Folklorico from Young Audiences of Houston (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n4 – 5 PM: Winding Paths of the Japanese Garden: Guided Tour (Japanese Garden)\n5 PM: “One Wan”: Japanese Garden Tea Ceremony (Japanese Garden)\n5 -6 PM: Perennials in the Park Tour (McGovern Centennial Gardens)\n5 – 8 PM: Hooked on Fishing! Youth Fishing with 4-H (Fishing Pier – The Commons)\n5 – 8 PM: DJ Areal: Music in the Commons (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n6 – 7 PM: A Walk Through Tranquility: Japanese Garden Tour (Japanese Garden)\n8:30 PM: Moonlight Movie Nights presented by Goya: The Parent Trap (Doreen Stoller Lawn – The Commons)\n\nSunday\, June 14 (3 – 9 p.m.): Family & Global Community Day \n\n3 PM: “One Wan”: Japanese Garden Tea Ceremony (Japanese Garden)\n4 – 5 PM: A Walk Through Tranquility: Japanese Garden Tour (Japanese Garden)\n5 PM: “One Wan”: Japanese Garden Tea Ceremony (Japanese Garden)\n5 – 6 PM: Mosaic Workshop from Young Audiences of Houston (Astros Foundation Pavilion – The Commons)\n5 – 6 PM: Bats-a-Billion: Discover the World of Bats (Cullen Pavilion – The Commons)\n6 – 7 PM: Winding Paths of the Japanese Garden: Guided Tour (Japanese Garden)\n7 – 9 PM: Jazz in the Park with Bayou City Jazz Band (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n\nWednesday\, June 17 (3 – 9 p.m.): Wellness in the Park – THIS DATE HAS BEEN CANCELED DUE TO INCLEMENT WEATHER! \nFriday\, June 19 (5 – 9 p.m.): Juneteenth Celebration \n\n5 – 6 PM: Kick Into Creativity by Eco Art Studio (Astros Foundation Pavilion – The Commons)\n5 – 6 PM: A Walk Through Tranquility: Japanese Garden Tour (Japanese Garden)\n5 – 7 PM: Carousel Karaoke (Lott Family Carousel – The Commons)\n6 – 7 PM: Voices from the Past: “Git” On Board – The Life of Harriet Tubman from Young Audiences of Houston (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n6 – 7 PM: Roses in Bloom Tour (McGovern Centennial Gardens)\n6 – 8 PM: Soccer for Success by Houston Parks and Recreation Department (Next to the Carousel and Play Areas in the Commons)\n7 – 9 PM: Open Decks: Live DJ Experience (Powell Foundation Terrace – Between Water Play Area and Space Adventure in the Commons)\n\nSaturday\, June 20 (3 – 10 p.m.): Global Rhythms \n\n3 – 4 PM: Trees for Texas: A Backyard Tree Walk (Astros Foundation Pavilion – The Commons)\n3 – 4 PM: Sonidos Sincopados with Jorge Orta from Young Audiences of Houston (Next to the Carousel and Play Areas in the Commons)\n3 – 6 PM: Pop-Up Performances (Miller Outdoor Theatre)\n4 – 5 PM: Beast Boogie (Anthony Silva) Dance Demo from Young Audiences of Houston (Next to the Carousel and Play Areas in the Commons)\n4 -5 PM: A Walk Through Tranquility: Japanese Garden Tour (Japanese Garden)\n5 – 6 PM: Perennials in the Park Tour (McGovern Centennial Gardens)\n5 – 8 PM: DJ Hiram: Music in the Commons (Next to the Carousel and Play Areas in the Commons)\n6 – 8 PM: Soccer for Success by Houston Parks and Recreation Department (Next to the Carousel and Play Areas in the Commons)\n8:30 PM: Moonlight Movie Nights presented by Goya: A Bug’s Life (Doreen Stoller Lawn – The Commons)\nAll Day: Goya Giveaways (Next to the Carousel and Play Areas in the Commons)\n\nSunday\, June 21 (3 – 9 p.m.): Community & Wellness Day \n\n3 – 4 PM: A Walk Through Tranquility: Japanese Garden Tour (Japanese Garden)\n3 – 7 PM: Activities with The Health Museum (Astros Foundation Pavilion – The Commons)\n4 – 5 PM: Make Your Own Mandala with Young Audiences of Houston (Next to the Carousel and Play Areas in the Commons)\n4 -5 PM: Origami in the Japanese Garden (Japanese Garden)\n4 – 8 PM: Kindstation by Be Kind (Cullen Pavilion – The Commons)\n5 – 6 PM: Wellness Walk with Urban Paths’ Laura Conely (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n5 – 6 PM: Roses in Bloom Tour (McGovern Centennial Gardens)\n6 – 7 PM: Pilates in the Park by Revival Pilates (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n6 – 8 PM: Soccer for Success by Houston Parks and Recreation Department (Next to the Carousel and Play Areas in the Commons)\n7 – 8 PM: Yoga in the Park by Black Swan Yoga (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n8 – 9 PM: Prioritizing Peace: Sound Bath (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n\nTuesday\, June 23 (3 – 9 p.m.): Youth + Play + Sustainability Day \nFriday\, June 26 (5 – 9 p.m.): Latin Night \nSaturday\, June 27 (3 – 10 p.m.): Global DJ Night \nSunday\, June 28 (3 – 9 p.m.): International Culture Day \nMonday\, June 29 (3 – 9 p.m.): Arts + Nature Day \nFriday\, July 3 (5 – 10 p.m.): Summer Nights in the Park \nSaturday\, July 4 (3 – 7 p.m.): Celebrate America – Houston Style \nSunday\, July 5 (3 – 9 p.m.): Closing Celebration \n+++ \nMOONLIGHT MOVIE NIGHTS\nPresented by Goya \n \nAs part of the summer offerings\, enjoy Moonlight Movie Nights\, presented by Goya\, in the Commons! Movies will start at approximately 8:30 p.m.\, around sunset. These movies are free and open to the public. \n\nSaturday\, June 13: The Parent Trap (1998; PG)\nSaturday\, June 20: A Bug’s Life (1998; G)\nSaturday\, June 27: Lilo & Stitch (2002; PG)\nFriday\, July 3: National Treasure (2004; PG)\n\nBe sure to get to the Commons early to snag your spot on the lawn. Guests are welcome to bring blankets or lawn chairs to settle in for the movie. \n+++ \nTo inquire about sponsorship opportunities and ways to get involved\, email community@hermannpark.org.
URL:https://hermannpark.org/event/kicking-it-at-hermann-park/
LOCATION:The Commons
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://hermannpark.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Kicking-it-at-the-Commons-Square.jpg
END:VEVENT
