SUMMARY:Moonlight Movie Nights: A Bug's Life
DESCRIPTION:As part of this summer’s Kicking It at Hermann Park offerings\, enjoy “Moonlight Movie Nights\,” presented by Goya\, in the Commons! On Saturday\, June 20\, join us for a showing of A Bug’s Life (1998 | G | 1h 35m runtime). \nThe movie will start at approximately 8:30 p.m.\, around sunset. The movie showing is free and open to the public. \nBe sure to get to the Commons early to snag your spot on the lawn. Guests are welcome to bring blankets or lawn chairs to settle in for the movie. \nFood and beverage will be available for purchase at the cafe and with food vendors on-site. \nThank you to Goya for their generous support!
URL:https://hermannpark.org/event/moonlight-movie-nights-the-parent-trap-2/
LOCATION:The Commons
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://hermannpark.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/P1011987-scaled-e1779221087349.jpg
